## G. Hard Output Contract
AG **không được** kết thúc slice bằng:
- chat summary only;
- `SLICE REVIEW DECISION`;
- `PASS TO LONG FINAL`;
- `READY FOR PRODUCTION ROLLOUT`.
Mọi execution slice phải kết thúc bằng **đúng một** trong:
```plain text
A) RUN_PAD_UPDATE appended to target, then short chat summary.
B) NOTION_APPEND_FAILED — FULL RUN_PAD_UPDATE BELOW, then full RUN_PAD_UPDATE in chat.
```
Thiếu → `BLOCKED / missing RUN_PAD_UPDATE`.
## H. Definition of Ready (per slice)
A slice is ready only if:
- [ ] [AGENTS.md](http://AGENTS.md) exists.
- [ ] Runtime sync passed after latest Notion updates.
- [ ] Workspace boundary confirmed.
- [ ] Current slice named.
- [ ] Output target confirmed.
- [ ] Allowed files listed.
- [ ] Forbidden actions listed.
- [ ] Commands approved.
- [ ] QA/evidence requirements clear.
- [ ] Human gate clear.
Thiếu một mục → `BLOCKED / not ready for execution`.
## I. Definition of Done (per slice)
A slice is done only if:
- [ ] RUN_PAD_UPDATE appended or full RUN_PAD_UPDATE pasted.
- [ ] Result là PASS / PARTIAL / FAIL.
- [ ] Files changed listed.
- [ ] Commands run listed.
- [ ] QA evidence listed.
- [ ] Screenshot/evidence paths listed when relevant.
- [ ] Scope/security check listed.
- [ ] Next action listed.
- [ ] AG did not self-assign review outcome.
Thiếu một mục → `BLOCKED / missing RUN_PAD_UPDATE evidence`.
## J. QA Matrix (15 groups)
Full QA Matrix gồm 15 group (A–O): visible text artifact, placeholder leakage, form-control visual-state, component state visual, route/navigation, interaction/state, product logic, layout/responsive, browser/runtime, accessibility, security/privacy/scope, SEO/metadata/polish, performance/asset, cross-browser/device, deployment-readiness.
QA commands chuẩn: `qa:static`, `build`, `qa:dist`, `qa:scope`, `qa:routes`, `qa:interactions`, `qa:screenshots`, `qa:product`, `qa:a11y`, `qa:cross-browser`, `qa:polish`, `qa:all-local`.
Optional/unavailable layer phải **explicit PARTIAL**, không silent skip.
**Anti-AI-Slop Visual QA (Group L extension).** Chạy như một phần của Group L — SEO/metadata/polish trước khi set `QA`:
- Không dùng gradient tím / "AI default color" nếu không có trong brand token.
- Không dùng animation bounce, pulse, float vô nghĩa.
- Spacing dùng đúng scale (4/8/16/24/32/48) — không spacing tự chọn.
- Font weight có hệ thống — không mix bold/regular tùy tiện.
- Button/CTA có hierarchy rõ — không phải tất cả đều to và đồng màu accent.
- Shadow/border-radius đồng nhất theo design token, không mỗi component một kiểu.
- Motion timing hợp lý: enter 150–300ms, exit nhanh hơn enter.
- Layout không bị "centered everything" — có visual tension, không flat.
- Không quá 3 tone màu chủ đạo trong một view.
- Không để placeholder text "Lorem ipsum" hoặc "Content goes here".
Chi tiết: <mention-page url="https://app.notion.com/p/778655b61eba82d69ded819e06c30d85">Website QA Master Plan — Full Error Coverage Matrix</mention-page> · <mention-page url="https://app.notion.com/p/853655b61eba83b28fa701009317738a">Website QA Error Taxonomy — Comprehensive</mention-page>.
## J.1. Taste System Gate — bắt buộc trước visual implementation
<callout icon="🎚️" color="purple_bg">
	Website Skill không chỉ build website chạy được. Website Skill phải giữ được **taste system đã duyệt**. Nếu taste chưa được định nghĩa, AG phải dừng trước khi triển khai visual lớn.
</callout>
### J.1.1. Design DNA Contract
Trước khi build website có giao diện public-facing, Tilog phải chốt một **Design DNA Contract** ngắn trong Website Contract hoặc Run Pad:
- **Brand feel:** ví dụ `premium editorial`, `quiet luxury`, `content-first`, `calm interface`.
- **Interface type:** editorial/content site, SaaS dashboard, landing conversion, documentation, learning hub…
- **Allowed visual patterns:** token màu, font, spacing, card, badge, tag, hero, imagery.
- **Disallowed visual patterns:** animation phô, icon thừa, CTA thừa, gradient/AI slop, centered-everything, hashtag social nếu không hợp ngữ cảnh.
- **Default decision:** nếu mơ hồ, chọn phương án **calmer / simpler / less decorative**.
Hard rule:
```plain text
If taste is undefined, stop before visual implementation.
If a component has no approved visual rule, use the quietest standard pattern.
```
### J.1.2. Motion Token Contract
Mọi website phải có motion policy tối thiểu. Default cho editorial/static content site:
```plain text
Allowed:
- opacity fade: 120–180ms
- border/background transition: 150–220ms
- card lift: max translateY(-2px) or -4px
- shadow increase: subtle only

Disallowed:
- bounce
- pulse
- float
- arrow glide
- text slide
- scale above 1.01 unless approved
- underline animation
- stagger animation that distracts from reading

Default:
- If motion is not essential to comprehension or affordance, remove it.
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion.
```
### J.1.3. Component Contract Library
Với các component lặp lại, Tilog phải ghi rule trước khi AG sửa:
```plain text
COMPONENT CONTRACT
- Purpose:
- Required content:
- Visible affordance:
- Hover/focus behavior:
- Mobile behavior:
- Motion:
- Do:
- Don't:
- Evidence required:
```
Các component thường cần contract:
- article/card;
- tag/chip/badge;
- hero;
- filter sheet;
- nav/header;
- CTA button;
- form/input;
- empty/error state.
### J.1.4. Component State Evidence Gate
Trước khi báo PASS cho visual slice, AG phải trả evidence cho state quan trọng:
```plain text
COMPONENT STATE EVIDENCE
- default state
- hover state
- keyboard focus state
- active/selected state if relevant
- mobile state
- dark/light variant if relevant
- reduced-motion behavior
```
Nếu thiếu state evidence:
```plain text
Status: PARTIAL — visual state evidence missing
```
Build pass, route pass, deploy pass **không đủ** để visual pass.
### J.1.5. Taste Recovery Mode
Dùng khi website chạy được nhưng “chưa sang”, “motion lạ”, “AI slop”, “visual noise”, “kém premium”.
Rules:
```plain text
You are in Taste Recovery Mode.

Goal:
Improve perceived taste without changing product logic.

Rules:
- Do not add new sections.
- Do not add decorative animation.
- Do not add icons unless explicitly required.
- Reduce visual noise before adding new elements.
- Prefer spacing, typography, contrast, and restraint.
- Change only the listed components.
- Build locally first.
- Deploy preview at most once after fixes.
- Return before/after notes and component state evidence.
```
Taste Recovery không được biến thành build lại website.
### J.1.6. Visual Fix Deploy Restraint
For visual fix slices:
```plain text
- Build locally first.
- Inspect locally.
- Deploy preview at most once after fixes.
- If visual is still uncertain, stop and return evidence.
- Do not repeatedly deploy to chase a better hash URL.
```
## J.2. Atlas-derived rule pack — reusable lesson
Từ case `trilong.vn/atlas`, thêm default rule cho editorial card/tag sites:
```plain text
EDITORIAL CARD DEFAULTS
- Whole card can be clickable.
- Do not add visible "Read more" / "Đọc tiếp" unless conversion requires it.
- Do not add arrow icons by default.
- No title underline on hover/focus.
- Hover max lift: 2–4px.
- No text shift.
- No protruding motion.
- Tags are metadata, not social hashtags, unless the brand explicitly wants social feel.
- Tags must remain readable on both dark and light cards.
- If card already communicates affordance, remove extra CTA.
```
Câu chốt:
```plain text
Website Skill does not only build working websites.
It builds websites that preserve the approved taste system.
If taste is undefined, stop before visual implementation.
```
## J.3. E-learning / Quiz Website Rule Pack — reusable lesson
Từ case `edu.banhmimahai.vn/hoinhap`, thêm default rule cho website học + test dùng dữ liệu từ Notion.
```plain text
E-LEARNING QUIZ DEFAULTS
- Notion/source document is the source of truth for question content when the contract says so.
- If source content is editable and wrong, fix the source before adding permanent runtime filters.
- Runtime cleanup is temporary only; remove it once generated data is clean, or document why it remains.
- Unanswered answer must be represented as null/undefined-safe null, never as the correct answer.
- Scoring must only count correct when selectedAnswer exists and selectedAnswer === correctAnswer.
- Result review must show all options, correct option, selected option if any, unanswered state if null, and explanation.
- If unanswered, do not highlight a fake wrong selected option; show a distinct "unanswered" banner/state.
- Question navigation/grid states must be mutually exclusive: active, answered, unanswered.
- Learning UI should prefer calm state tints/borders over decorative stars, gold badges, or importance markers unless explicitly approved.
- Use static-first for self-study/test-in-browser flows; escalate to Full-Stack mode only when the contract requires login, centralized attempt storage, admin dashboard, retake policy enforcement, or reporting sync.
```
Hard invariant:
```plain text
unanswered !== correct
unanswered !== selected wrong option
unanswered = null and must be reviewable
```
